3 Things to know before buying your perfect jeans

1. The rise- Most overlooked but most important. High waist is perfect for all body types. Choose high waist when in doubt.

2. Right size- Choose the right size to feel comfortable through the day. Right size looks flattering and neat. Quick tip- You should be able to run 1 finger through your waist.
Choosing jeans with 1% or 2% will always give you more ease.

items.Video_Title: GOOD AMERICAN X ZARA JEANS CURVY PLUS SIZE TRY ON HAUL | IS IT WORTH IT?👖
items.Video_Description:
Want the REAL tea on the new @Goodamerican X ZARA denim collaboration? Look no further friends because I went ahead and brought all the denim jeans in the collection so you don't have to! 👖

I have always been super curious about trying out Good American denim jeans but the price has always been way too high for me to justify but because I love ya'll I went ahead and brought some to see if they are infact size-inclusive and peach approved! 🍑

While Zara is known for having a huge selection of denim styles, the store doesn’t have the greatest sizing options. Most items only run up to a Large or Extra Large and I can attest that the sizing is consistently inconsistent but it seems as if the retailer is finally listening to the pleas for more inclusive and consistent sizing. This is where Good American comes in. 

For background, Good American was founded by @Khloekardashian and Emma Grede to bring high-quality, size-inclusive options to the fashion industry, specifically in denim wear. Since launching in 2016, Good American has expanded its collection beyond just denim and now also sells ready-to-wear, swim, shoes, and athletic apparel—all in sizes 00-32+. I’ve been a fan of Good American’s collections because they manage to address both trendy items (like baggy skater jeans) and wardrobe staples that can become the go-to for any event.

The Good American x Zara collaboration follows the same inclusive principles that Good American was founded on and offers pieces at a more accessible price point—all the items range from $35.90 - to $99.90. Despite the lower price point, the items have a high-fashion feel. The basis of the collaboration is focused on denim. 

The collection includes four styles of jeans - classic slim, high-rise skinny, ‘90s relaxed, and classic bootcut and has the gap-proof waistbands and stretchy fabric that Good American is known for. All jeans are priced at $69.95 (a pair of Good American jeans usually runs at around $150) and are available in sizes 00-30 US a significant expansion on Zara’s usual size range. Each piece is made with raw materials that aim to reduce environmental impact like ecologically grown or recycled cotton.

ZARA DENIM TRY ON HAUL | NEW 2022 COLLECTION

This is Zara Denim Try on Haul video, I will be trying on jeans from Zara's new 2022 collection.  I've purchased all the new in Zara denim styles and giving you my honest opinion.  I hope by purchasing every style of Zara denim 2022 collection and trying them on, it will give you an idea of how each pair of jeans will look on you.  Purchasing Zara denim can be difficult, especially when you are not able to try them on.  In this video, I'll be doing all the hard work for you by trying on every new style of Zara denim.  I'll be reviewing every new style and letting you know how fit and the quality of each pair of jeans. This video will help you determine which Zara denim style is worth buying and which Zara denim style is not. 

Below are my measurements to give you an idea of how each zara denim will look on you compared to my body type.  I am 5'5 and I weigh 105 pounds.  I would consider myself to be petite.  I have a longer torso and shorter legs so when I'm buying zara denim, they have to be petite friendly for my legs.  I look for Zara denim that will elongate my legs and balance out my petite proportions.  I always wear high waisted jeans to help balance my body proportions.  Since I my legs are petite, jeans tend to be very long on me.  Therefore, it's important that the Zara jeans is not too long for my petite legs.
